olive oil
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
2 clove garlic
1 tbs soy sauce
1 sachet sesame seeds
1 bag baby spinach leaves
½ packet Yuzu Vinaigrette
1 packet mayonnaise
2 tbs plain flour
1 tsp salt
1 egg
¾ packet panko breadcrumbs
1 packet chicken breast strips
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 drizzle rice wine vinegar

Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Place the peeled & chopped pumpkin on a lined oven tray. Sprinkle over 1/2 the sesame seeds. Drizzle with olive oil and toss to coat. Roast until tender, 20-25 minutes. Meanwhile, finely chop the garlic. In a small bowl, combine the garlic and soy sauce. In the last 5 minutes of cook time, pour the soy-garlic mixture over the pumpkin. Return to the oven and roast until tender and caramelised.

While the pumpkin is roasting, roughly chop the baby spinach leaves. In a second small bowl, combine the yuzu vinaigrette (see ingredients) and mayonnaise. Season to taste and set aside.

In a shallow bowl, combine the plain flour and the salt. In a second shallow bowl, whisk the egg. In a third shallow bowl, place the panko breadcrumbs (see ingredients) and the remaining sesame seeds. Coat the chicken breast strips in the flour mixture, followed by the egg, and finally the panko breadcrumbs. Transfer to a plate.

In a large frying pan, add enough olive oil to cover the base and heat over a medium-high heat. Cook the crumbed chicken in batches until golden and cooked through, 2-4 minutes each side. Transfer to a plate lined with paper towel.

TIP: Add extra oil if needed so the schnitzel does not stick to the pan.

While the chicken is cooking, combine the shredded cabbage mix, baby spinach, a drizzle of rice wine vinegar and olive oil in a large bowl. Season to taste.

Divide the sesame crusted chicken, soy-garlic pumpkin and spinach slaw between plates. Serve with the yuzu mayo.